Choice between VDS and VPS

Because they are both very similar, let us consider their differences and see which is better. The main differences have been in the operating systems being utilized in VDS and VPS. Hyper Visor was created to be used around the Windows Enterprise Edition and Server 2008 Standard. An array of Linux and Unix options together with any Windows OS may be used to run this application, similar to the web server, Apache. VPS has similar capabilities although VDS might be more suited for larger web sites and applications needing more memory.

